flowchart TB
    A[Start Workflow] --> B[For each service]
    B --> C{package-lock.json exists?}
    C -- No --> C1[Skip service]
    C -- Yes --> D[npm ci]
    D --> E[npm audit]

    E -->|No vulnerabilities| F[Skip service]
    E -->|Vulnerabilities found| G[Safe fix: npm audit fix]

    G --> H[npm audit]
    H -->|Still vulnerable| I{Direct vulns are devDependencies only?}
    H -->|Resolved or reduced| J[Continue]

    I -- Yes --> K[Force fix: npm audit fix --force]
    I -- No --> K1[Skip force fix]
    K --> L[npm audit]
    K1 --> L

    L -->|Still vulnerable| M[Dynamic override for eligible transitive deps]
    L -->|Resolved or reduced| N[Continue]

    M --> M1{Override written?}
    M1 -- Yes --> M2[npm install]
    M1 -- No --> N
    M2 --> N

    N --> O[Downgrade guard: deps/devDeps/optional/peer/overrides]
    O --> O1{Any downgrade detected?}
    O1 -- Yes --> O2[Restore original spec + npm install]
    O1 -- No --> P
    O2 --> P

    P{git diff package.json or package-lock.json?}
    P -- No --> P1[No dependency changes]
    P -- Yes --> Q[Validate changes]

    Q --> R{test script exists?}
    R -- Yes --> S[npm run test]
    R -- No --> T[Accept changes]

    S -->|Pass| T
    S -->|Fail| U[Revert package.json + package-lock.json]

    T --> X[Mark changes found]

    X --> Y[Create/Update PR]
    Y --> Z[Attempt auto-merge after CI]

    classDef decision fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#666,stroke-width:1px;
    class C,I,M1,O1,P,R decision;
